      "properties": {
        "Node name for S&R": "Note"
      },
      "widgets_values": [
        "ATLAS INPUT QUICKSTART — image in, projected relief out.\n\nDefaults = instant relief: one high-res mesh, first queue in seconds. Then grow into the master workflow's behaviors without leaving this node:\n\n· layers 2–4 — depth-band clean-plate layers (watertight splits)\n· use_vlm — the 🧭 assessment configures prompts/geometry/bands per image (forces 4 bands)\n· sky + sky_prompt — SAM sky card (needs ComfyUI-RMBG)\n· scope_prompts — one SAM prompt per band, far→near; self-disarming on no-match\n· inpaint (+ upscale_model) — per-band LaMa clean plates (needs comfyui-inpaint-nodes + big-lama.pt)\n\nMissing packs never error — features skip and the report output says so. When you outgrow this node: examples/atlas_camera_staged_master_workflow.json is the same logic with stages, gates and per-layer debug.\n\nDCC EXPORTS (Nuke / Maya / USD):\n- AtlasExportUSD writes the CAMERA (camera.usda) — works at any layers setting (needs the [usd] extra: pip install atlas-camera[usd]).\n- AtlasExportNukeLayers / MayaLayers export the PROJECTION LAYERS (per-band cameras + geometry + plates + mattes). They need ProjectionSources, so set AtlasInput 'layers' >= 1 (2/3/4). At layers=0 (instant single relief) they gracefully skip with a note — set layers>=1 for the full DCC handoff."
      ]
    },
